Uses of Package
org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics

  • Packages that use org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics 
    Package Description
    org.sbml.squeezer
    This is the core of SBMLsqueezer as it contains the central classes for reaction type analysis, kineticl law generation and some specialized exceptions.
    org.sbml.squeezer.gui
    This package contains all necessary classes for the graphical user interface.
    org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics
    This package contains one class for each supported kinetic law.
  • Classes in org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics used by org.sbml.squeezer 
    Class and Description
    BasicKineticLaw
    An abstract super class of specialized kinetic laws, which provides methods for creating Parameter and UnitDefinition objects and maintains all these in dedicated lists.

    The possible selections for the three versions of modular rate laws (cf.
  • Classes in org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics used by org.sbml.squeezer.gui 
    Class and Description
    BasicKineticLaw
    An abstract super class of specialized kinetic laws, which provides methods for creating Parameter and UnitDefinition objects and maintains all these in dedicated lists.
  • Classes in org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics used by org.sbml.squeezer.kinetics 
    Class and Description
    AdditiveModelLinear
    This class creates an equation based on a linear additive model.
    AdditiveModelNonLinear
    This class creates an equation based on a non-linear additive model.
    BasicKineticLaw
    An abstract super class of specialized kinetic laws, which provides methods for creating Parameter and UnitDefinition objects and maintains all these in dedicated lists.
    GeneralizedMassAction
    This class creates rate equations according to the generalized mass action rate law.
    InterfaceArbitraryEnzymeKinetics
    Kinetic law objects that implement this interface are able to describe any enzyme-catalyzed process whether or not an enzyme is explicitely assigned to the reaction.
    InterfaceBiBiKinetics
    Kinetic law objects that implement this interface are able to describe enzyme-catalyzed reactions with exactly two reactants (or one reactant with a stoichiometry of two) and two products (or one product with a stoichiometry of two).
    InterfaceBiUniKinetics
    A kinetic law object that implements this interface is able to describe enzyme-catalyzed reactions with two reactants or one reactant with a stoichiometry of two and exactly one product with stoichiometry of one.
    InterfaceGeneRegulatoryKinetics
    A kinetic law object that implements this interface is able to describe gene regulatory processes, i.e., transcription and translation.
    InterfaceIntegerStoichiometry
    All implementing classes represent kinetic equations that require all participating species to take part with integer stoichiometry (reactants and products).
    InterfaceIrreversibleKinetics
    All implementing kinetic laws can be applied to irreversible reactions.
    InterfaceKinteticsType
    Common super type for all interfaces that declare kinetics types.
    InterfaceModulatedKinetics
    All implementing kinetic laws allow activatiors or inhibitors to take part in the reaction process.
    InterfaceNonEnzymeKinetics
    If a kinetic law object implements this interface, it can be applied to reactions that are catalyzed by species that are not an enzyme.
    InterfaceReversibleKinetics
    All implementing kinietic laws can be applied to reversible reactions.
    InterfaceUniUniKinetics
    A kinetic law that implements this interface can be applied to enzyme-catalyzed reactions with exactly one reactant with stoichiometry one and exactly one product with stoichiometry one.
    InterfaceZeroProducts
    Kinetics that allow for an empty list of products.
    InterfaceZeroReactants
    Kinetics that allow for an empty list of reactants.
    PowerLawModularRateLaw
    Represents the power-law modular rate law (PM) from Liebermeister et al.
    TypeStandardVersion
    The possible selections for the three versions of modular rate laws (cf.
